===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|truht|lang=ang}}, in part from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|truite|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|tructa|lang=la}}, perhaps from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|τρώκτης|sc=polytonic|tr=trōktēs||nibbler|lang=grc}}, from {{term|τρώγω|sc=polytonic|tr=trōgō||I gnaw|lang=grc}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|tere-|to rub, to turn|lang=en}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|pl=trout|pl2=trouts}}

# Any of several species of [[fish]] in [[Salmonidae]], closely related to [[salmon]], and distinguished by [[spawn]]ing more than once.
#: ''Many anglers consider '''trout''' to be the archetypical quarry.''
# {{context|British|pejoratives}} An [[elderly]] [[woman]] of [[dubious]] [[sensibilities]].
#: ''Look, you silly old '''trout'''; you can't keep bringing home cats!  You can't afford the ones you have!''

